$$\left(\frac{5}{3},2\pi\right)=\{x|\frac{5}{3}<x<2\pi\}$$

The whole numbers in this interval are 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, ..., 6. Therefore, there are 6 whole numbers in the interval.

Final Answer: $\boxed{6}$. I hope it is correct
